7600	  wide fibre power of \(\coprod_i X_i \to S\) over \(S\) decomposes as
7601	  \[
7602	    \bigl(\textstyle\coprod_{i} X_i\bigr)^{\times_S 1}
7603	      \;\cong\;
7604	    \coprod_{\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(1) \to \iota} X_{\sigma(0)},
7605	  \]
7606	  the \(\sigma\)-component being the \(1\)-fold fibre power \(X_{\sigma(0)}\).
7607	\end{lemma}
7608	\begin{proof}
7609	  \uses{lem:widePullback_overX_eq_prod}
7610	  By Lemma~\ref{lem:widePullback_overX_eq_prod} the \(1\)-fold fibre power is the \(1\)-fold product
7611	  in \(\operatorname{Over} S\), which is the object itself: \((\coprod_i X_i)^{\times_S 1} \cong
7612	  \coprod_i X_i\). On the right, the evaluation-at-\(0\) bijection \(\mathrm{Fin}(1) \to \iota\)
7613	  \(\;\cong\;\) \(\iota\) identifies \(\coprod_{\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(1)\to\iota} X_{\sigma(0)}\)
7614	  with \(\coprod_i X_i\) (reindexing a coproduct along a bijection of index types). Composing the
7615	  two gives the claim --- the trivial reindexing.
7616	\end{proof}
